基思·理查兹说滚石乐队的“哈克尼钻石”是由米克·贾格尔的“焦虑”推动的https://www.nme.com/news/music/keith-richards-says-rolling-stones-hackney-diamonds-was-fuelled-by-mick-jaggers-angst-3513011?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=keith-理查兹说滚石乐队哈克尼钻石是由米克贾格斯的焦虑推动的Tom SkinnerWed, 11 Oct 2023 10:49:38 +0000 Music NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3513011 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="滚石乐队的罗尼·伍德、米克·贾格尔和基思·理查兹" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>乐队近二十年来的第一张唱片将于下周发行</p><p>基思<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/keith-richards-says-rolling-stones-hackney-diamonds-was-fuelled-by-mick-jaggers-angst-3513011">·理查兹 (Keith Richards) 称滚石乐队 (Rolling Stones) 的“哈克尼钻石”(Hackney Diamonds) 是由米克·贾格尔 (Mick Jagger) 的“焦虑”推动的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="滚石乐队的罗尼·伍德、米克·贾格尔和基思·理查兹" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/TheRollingStones-Keith-Richards-interview-Mick-Jagger-angst-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/keith-richards">基思·理查兹 (Keith Richards)</a>表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">，滚石乐队</a>即将推出的专辑<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">“Hackney Diamonds”</a>是由米克·贾格尔 ( <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mick-jagger">Mick Jagger</a> ) 的“焦虑”推动的。</p><p>这支标志性乐队将于 10 月 20 日发行他们的第 24 张录音室唱片 -<a href="https://therollingstones.lnk.to/HackneyDiamondsPR" target="_blank" rel="noopener">您可以在此处预订</a>。继 2005 年的<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-the-rolling-stones-7763-312997#:~:text=This%20is%20an%20old%2Dfashioned,well%20be%20by%20Sheryl%20Crow.">《A Bigger Bang》</a>之后，这张唱片将标志着滚石乐队 18 年来首张原创音乐合集。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-rolling-stones-new-album-release-date-hackney-diamonds-3494545">滚石乐队的回归带来了更大的冲击</a></strong></li></ul><p>贾格尔等人已经分享了“Hackney Diamonds”中的两首单曲： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">“Angry”</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-share-lady-gaga-and-stevie-wonder-featuring-new-single-sweet-sounds-of-heaven-3506066">“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven”</a> （由<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-working-with-lady-gaga-for-rolling-stones-sweet-sounds-of-heaven-3506722">Lady Gaga</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>演唱）。</p><p>昨天（10 月 10 日）在接受 BBC 广播四台采访时，理查兹谈到了该乐队新材料背后的主题。当被问及即将发行的专辑中贯穿的愤怒感时，吉他手说这是贾格尔写作时情绪的结果。</p><p> “米克写了歌词，”理查兹解释道（来自<a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/keith-richards-mick-jagger-angry-rolling-stones-b2427069.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《独立报》</em></a> ）。 “他内心有些焦虑，他可能想‘让我们利用它吧’。”</p><p>他继续说道：“米克，一首他并不真正感兴趣的歌曲确实会让事情变得很糟糕（笑）。这也许是花了 18 年时间的原因之一——因为米克的热情来来去去。”</p><p>此外，理查兹在谈话中指出贾格尔是如何推动滚石乐队录制新音乐的成员。</p><p> “米克是推动者，”他解释道。 “在上次巡演结束时，他第一次击中了我的正确位置。他说，‘我一直想在乐队一离开公路就尽快录制，因为他们是一支被润滑的乐队’。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="滚石乐队 |甜美的天籁之音|壮举。 Lady Gaga 与史蒂维旺德 |可视化工具" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JnKG00M87e0?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>理查兹告诉电视台，该乐队<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/the-rolling-stones-live-madrid-review-setlist-sixty-tour-3238910">去年庆祝了成立 60 周年</a>，计划明年“如果每个人都还站着的话”将这张专辑推出去。目前尚未公布巡演日期。</p><p> “哈克尼钻石”还将包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-says-paul-mccartney-really-rocked-it-on-rolling-stones-collaboration-3502352">保罗·麦卡特尼</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰</a>和前滚石乐队贝斯手比尔·怀曼的贡献。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-reveal-charlie-watts-appears-on-two-tracks-of-new-album-hackney-diamonds-3494170">两首歌——“Mess It Up”和“Live By The Sword”——由他们已故的鼓手查理·瓦茨 (Charlie Watts) 演唱</a>。</p><p>在其他新闻中， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-says-paul-mccartney-really-rocked-it-on-rolling-stones-collaboration-3502352">贾格尔在接受采访时解释了披头士乐队偶像麦卡特尼是如何登上唱片的</a>。</p><p> “我们建议他演奏这首朋克曲调，”他说。 “我不知道结果如何，但他真的很震撼，而且他喜欢这样做。他说：“和乐队一起演奏真是太棒了！和乐队一起演奏真的很愉快。”</p><p>与此同时， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-are-already-working-on-their-next-album-3498047">贾格尔最近证实滚石乐队已经开始制作他们的下一张完整作品</a>。</p><p>基思<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/keith-richards-says-rolling-stones-hackney-diamonds-was-fuelled-by-mick-jaggers-angst-3513011">·理查兹 (Keith Richards) 称滚石乐队 (Rolling Stones) 的“哈克尼钻石”(Hackney Diamonds) 是由米克·贾格尔 (Mick Jagger) 的“焦虑”推动的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
